Proposed Changes
We will build the website within the existing portfolio-website directory, which is already linked to your GitHub and Vercel.

Core Architecture
Framework: React + Vite (already initialized).
Styling: CSS variables and vanilla CSS, strictly adhering to the typography, spacing, and monochrome color palette defined in DESIGN.md (Bigpicture Company style).
Routing: React Router for navigating between the Homepage and individual Project Pages.
Layout & Visuals
Implement the 1440px max-width editorial layout with 72px section gaps.
Use Helvetica Neue for display typography and PPSupplyMono for meta labels (or their specified substitutes).
No chromatic color. Only the 5 defined neutrals.
Add the crumpled paper texture to the background as described in DESIGN.md.
Project Navigation
Build a custom horizontal carousel/dial for project navigation on the Homepage.
Include smooth weighted transitions and scaling based on distance from the center.
Content Integration
Parse the PDFs to generate JSON data for each project.
Migrate the images found in the workspace into the public/ directory and organize them by project.
Construct dedicated Project Pages with semantic sections (Hero, Context, Problem, Research, etc.).
Verification Plan
Automated Checks
Run npm run build to ensure the project compiles successfully without TypeScript or Vite errors.
Ensure 60fps scrolling and smooth animations via manual checks on the local dev server.
Manual Verification
Deploy to Vercel (automatically triggered by pushing to the main branch).
Review the live Vercel URL to confirm the visual styling matches DESIGN.md perfectly.
Ensure the horizontal project navigation behaves like a physical dial across devices.
